title: [MOD冲突]关于矿石菌种与神话生物等模组冲突
author: MC丁丁君
txt_content: 各位大佬，为什么矿石菌种加上关于怪物

replies.author: xmdhs
replies.txt_content:
删除 mod  MLPMod

所以是某个 mod 不肯让 forge 分配 id ，而是自己指定了一个 id 导致的崩溃咯。

https://www.minecraftforum.net/f ... mentexception-id-is
I've seen this bug hundreds of times. Look at the exact error:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: ID is already registered: 89

Headcrumbs mod is reporting that the ID it tried to use is already taken by something else. This should not happen because Forge is supposed to manage entity IDs for mods, to avoid conflicts. It's been like this since Minecraft 1.4.x. But some authors bypass Forge's entity assignemnt system in 1.7.x for whatever reason. What happens is (rough description):

Mod A is bypassing Forge auto system and registers entity ID 89 to itself.

At the same time Headcrumbs sends a request to Forge for a free entity ID. Forge says use ID 89 (because mod A did not inform Forge what it is doing). Headcrumbs tries to register ID 89, sees it's already taken, and crashes throwing that error.

Checking if Headcrums has configurable entity IDs in the config files will get you nothing, it uses Forge's auto system. Reporting this to headcrumbs author will probably end up with him/her telling you this should not happen because they use Forge auto assignment. Removing Headcrumbs will most likely cause another mod using Forge's auto system to crash with the same error, because they'll try to register an ID taken over by that "other" mod.
